from functools import lru_cache


@lru_cache(None)
def gt(x, l, r):
    if x[l]>x[r]


    i = l
    j = r
    while i < len(x) and j < len(x):
        if x[i] < x[j]:
            return r
        elif x[i] > x[j]:
            return l
        else:
            i += 1
            j += 1
    return l


def lss(x, s, e):
    if s + 1 < e:
        mid = (s + e) // 2
        l = lss(x, s, mid)
        r = lss(x, mid, e)
        return l if gt(x, l, r) else r
    else:
        return s


class Solution:
    def lastSubstring(self, s: str) -> str:
        ans = lss(s, 0, len(s))
        return s[ans:]
